# Conventional Commits

Follow [Conventional Commits v1.0.0](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/#specification). PR titles to `dev` / `main` are validated in `.github/workflows/lint-pr-title.yml`; local commits should match so rebases and squash merges stay consistent.

## Format

```
<type>[optional scope][optional !]: <description>
```

- **type** (required): `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `style`, `refactor`, `perf`, `test`, `build`, `ci`, `chore`, `revert`
- **scope** (optional): area in parentheses, e.g. `feat(web):`, `fix(api):`, `chore(ci):`
- **!** (optional): breaking change, e.g. `feat!: remove legacy endpoint`
- **description**: imperative, lowercase start after the colon (project style), no trailing period on the subject line

## Examples

```text
feat(web): add run detail planning panel
fix(llm): handle missing API key when provider is unset
docs: link security policy from readme
chore: bump lockfile
ci: cache pip in workflow
```

## Avoid

```text
web: add panel
Remove old retention code
WIP
```

Use `feat(web):` / `fix(web):` / `chore:` instead of bare scopes or untyped sentences.
